OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1775811900
OL,3,CExtra police funding to keep people
OL,4,Csafe where they live, work and worship
OL,6,FPolice are to be given an extra #5
OL,7,Fmillion to pay for more patrols around
OL,8,Fplaces of worship.
OL,10,FThe Home Office funding follows a
OL,11,Fterror attack on a synagogue in
OL,12,FManchester in October 2025 - and an
OL,13,Falleged arson attack in Golders Green,
OL,14,FNorth West London, where four Jewish
OL,15,Fcommunity ambulances were set alight
OL,16,Fin March.
OL,18,FSecurity Minister Dan Jarvis said the
OL,19,Fmoney would help "keep people safe in
OL,20,Fthe places where they live, work and
OL,21,Fworship".
OL,26,@{D@ROU}D@HO]
